Ready to take on digital accessibility?

DiAX improves and reports on the accessibility of digital applications and media including websites, apps, documents, and videoâ€™s.

How can DiAX help you?

Our IAAP certified experts provide:

  • Awareness through events
  • Training
  • Audits for certification or expert reviews
  • User testing with persons with a disability
  • Advice and coaching
  • Production, remediation, and operational support

Thanks to our framework agreements, many organisations and governments are able to use our services without the hassle of a public procurement procedure.

These are our framework agreements

Who is DiAX?

DiAX is a cooperation of experts in digital accessibility:

  • AnySurfer (Blindenzorg Licht & Liefde, nonprofit)
  • Eleven Ways
  • VeBeS (Vereniging van Blinden en Slechtzienden, nonprofit)

In legal terms, DiAX is a project of the nonprofit Koninklijke Maatschappij voor Blinden en Slechtzienden (KMBS)

These organisations rely on the expertise of DiAX
